snippet.textDisplay:
Musical version is amazing. Singer's rendering is average compared to Runa Laila..the best version (yes, better than Mehdi Hasan).

Why didn't Runa finish the last hardest-hitting verse after the music interlude?????
ab tak dil-e-ḳhush-fahm ko tujh se haiñ ummīdeñ 
ye āḳhirī sham.eñ bhī bujhāne ke liye aa 

The translation (as best as can be done from Urdu poetry to english without using too many of own words! )...

1. Yes, you have annoyance (towards me), 
                                                           if only to hurt my feelings, come
     Come, even if to leave me again, come
2. Keep at least some pretension of my Love's ego
     Sometimes, you too, to placate me, come
3. Relations may not be the same as before
    (at least) to fulfill the tradition-and-way of the world , come
4. To whom all will we explain the reason of separation
     You are angry with me, at least for the sake of society, come 
5. For a long age (I) am deprived of the joy of Crying
    O comfort of (my) soul, to make me cry, come
6. Even now (my) optimistic heart has hopes from/about you
    These last candles.. to extinguish them... Come !!!
